This log shows a **different failure** than the partner-repository one.

The important lines are:

```text
Required request parameter 'code' is not present
```

and

```text
java.lang.IllegalStateException: Invalid or expired state
```

and

```text
AuthService.handleCallback(...)
AuthController.callback(...)
```

### What is happening?

Your callback endpoint is probably something like:

```java
@GetMapping("/callback")
public ...
```

expecting:

```text
/auth/callback?code=xxxx&state=yyyy
```

But the request arriving is:

```text
/auth/callback?state=...
```

Notice:

```text
Required request parameter 'code' is not present
```

So Keycloak/OIDC did not send the authorization code, or the callback URL was manually refreshed/reused.

Then Arthur Core tries to validate:

```java
state
```

against Redis:

```text
lookup auth transaction key=...
found=null
```

and throws:

```text
Invalid or expired state
```

---

## Should this show your generic error page?

Yes.

This is a perfect candidate for:

```text
/arthur-core/error/technical
```

because the user cannot recover themselves.

---

## Better architecture

I would create:

```java
@ControllerAdvice
@Slf4j
public class UiExceptionHandler {

    @ExceptionHandler(IllegalStateException.class)
    public ModelAndView handleIllegalState(
            IllegalStateException ex) {

        return new ModelAndView(
                "redirect:/error/technical");
    }

    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)
    public ModelAndView handleGeneric(
            Exception ex) {

        return new ModelAndView(
                "redirect:/error/technical");
    }
}
```

Then:

```java
@Controller
public class ErrorController {

    @GetMapping("/error/technical")
    public ModelAndView technicalError() {
        ...
    }

    @GetMapping("/error/no-sales-point")
    public ModelAndView noSalesPoint() {
        ...
    }
}
```

---

## One thing I would improve

Instead of throwing:

```java
throw new IllegalStateException(
        "Invalid or expired state");
```

create:

```java
public class InvalidStateException
        extends RuntimeException {

    public InvalidStateException(String message) {
        super(message);
    }
}
```

Then:

```java
throw new InvalidStateException(
        "Invalid or expired state");
```

And handle it specifically:

```java
@ExceptionHandler(InvalidStateException.class)
public ModelAndView handleInvalidState(
        InvalidStateException ex) {

    return new ModelAndView(
            "redirect:/error/technical");
}
```

This makes the code much easier to understand than using generic `IllegalStateException`.

### So for your current Arthur Core flow

You now have three error categories:

| Error                                   | Location                   | Page            |
| --------------------------------------- | -------------------------- | --------------- |
| Invalid/expired callback state          | AuthController/AuthService | Technical Error |
| Partner Repository 500 / user not found | AuthService                | Technical Error |
| No sales points returned                | SalesPointController       | No Sales Point  |

Everything else can fall back to the generic technical error page.
